sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    %% Flow 1: TrustyAI Service Model Monitoring
    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over Client,TASApp: Flow 1: TrustyAI Service Model Monitoring
        participant Client as External Client
        participant TASRoute as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
        participant TASTLS as TAS TLS Service<br/>443/TCP HTTPS Reencrypt
        participant TASKRBP as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS (serving cert)
        participant TASApp as TrustyAI App<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

        Client->>TASRoute: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS
        TASRoute->>TASTLS: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS Reencrypt
        TASTLS->>TASKRBP: HTTPS/8443<br/>Bearer Token (TokenReview)
        TASKRBP->>TASApp: HTTP/8080<br/>localhost (no auth)
    end

    %% Flow 2: LMEval Job Execution
    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over User,OCI: Flow 2: LMEval Job Execution
        participant User as User
        participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
        participant LMESCtrl as LMES Controller
        participant InitC as Init Container<br/>(driver copy)
        participant MainC as Main Container<br/>(evaluation)
        participant Driver as ta-lmes-driver<br/>18080/TCP HTTP
        participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
        participant OCI as OCI Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

        User->>K8sAPI: Create LMEvalJob CR<br/>Bearer Token
        K8sAPI->>LMESCtrl: Watch event
        LMESCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Pod<br/>ServiceAccount
        K8sAPI-->>InitC: Start init container
        InitC->>InitC: Copy driver binary<br/>to shared volume
        InitC-->>MainC: Volume ready
        MainC->>Driver: GET /GetStatus<br/>HTTP/18080 localhost
        Driver-->>MainC: Status + progress
        LMESCtrl->>Driver: Pod exec → GET /GetStatus<br/>HTTP/18080
        Driver-->>LMESCtrl: Job status
        MainC->>S3: Download assets (optional)<br/>HTTPS/443 AWS IAM
        MainC->>OCI: Upload results (optional)<br/>HTTPS/443 credentials
    end

    %% Flow 3: GuardrailsOrchestrator Auto-Configuration
    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over GClient,DetectorISVC: Flow 3: GuardrailsOrchestrator Auto-Config
        participant GClient as Client
        participant GORCHRoute as GORCH Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
        participant GORCHKRBP as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8432/TCP HTTPS
        participant Orchestrator as Orchestrator<br/>8032/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS (serving cert)
        participant GORCHCtrl as GORCH Controller
        participant GenISVC as Generation Model<br/>(KServe ISVC)
        participant DetectorISVC as Detector Models<br/>(KServe ISVCs)

        GORCHCtrl->>K8sAPI: List InferenceServices<br/>ServiceAccount
        K8sAPI-->>GORCHCtrl: ISVCs with guardrails=true
        GORCHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create/Update ConfigMap<br/>(SHA256 hash tracking)
        GClient->>GORCHRoute: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS
        GORCHRoute->>GORCHKRBP: HTTPS/8432<br/>Bearer Token
        GORCHKRBP->>Orchestrator: HTTPS/8032<br/>TLS (serving cert)
        Orchestrator->>GenISVC: Inference request<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
        Orchestrator->>DetectorISVC: Detection request<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    end

    %% Flow 4: EvalHub Job Failure Reporting
    rect rgb(255, 230, 245)
        Note over FailReconciler,EvalHubAPI: Flow 4: EvalHub Job Failure Reporting
        participant FailReconciler as Failure Reconciler
        participant EvalHubAPI as EvalHub API<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS (service CA)
        participant KueueReconciler as Kueue Workload<br/>Reconciler

        FailReconciler->>K8sAPI: Watch Jobs/Pods<br/>ServiceAccount
        K8sAPI-->>FailReconciler: Job failure event<br/>(OOM, ImagePull, Crash)
        FailReconciler->>EvalHubAPI: POST /api/v1/.../events<br/>Bearer Token (SA)<br/>X-Tenant header
        KueueReconciler->>K8sAPI: Watch Workloads<br/>ServiceAccount
        K8sAPI-->>KueueReconciler: Workload failure
        KueueReconciler->>EvalHubAPI: POST failure event<br/>Bearer Token (SA)
    end
